  description:`Oktoberfest is the world's largest folk festival, drawing over six million visitors to Munich's Theresienwiese each year for 16 days of beer, food, music and Bavarian culture. Founded in 1810 to celebrate the marriage of Crown Prince Ludwig, Oktoberfest has grown into a global phenomenon that defines Munich's identity.\n\nThe festival features 14 large beer tents and 21 smaller tents, each with its own character and atmosphere. The six major Munich breweries — Augustiner, Hacker-Pschorr, Hofbräu, Löwenbräu, Paulaner and Spaten — each operate their own spectacular tents seating thousands. Traditional Bavarian food — roast chicken, pretzels, Hendl, Schweinshaxe — is served alongside vast quantities of freshly brewed Märzen.\n\nFor vendors, Oktoberfest represents the most competitive and prestigious event in Germany's festival calendar. The Theresienwiese outside the tents hosts hundreds of traditional fairground rides, food stalls and souvenir sellers. Applications for vendor spots open 18 months in advance and competition is fierce — a confirmed spot at Oktoberfest is a career-defining achievement for any food or craft vendor.\n\nBeyond the main festival, the surrounding city comes alive with Oktoberfest-themed events, popup markets and cultural activities throughout the two-week period, creating exceptional trading opportunities across Munich.`,
