  description:`Cologne hosts seven distinct Christmas markets across the city, but the most famous is the Cathedral Christmas Market (Kölner Dom Weihnachtsmarkt) directly in front of the magnificent Cologne Cathedral — a UNESCO World Heritage site. The backdrop of the soaring Gothic cathedral, spectacularly illuminated at night, creates one of the most photographed Christmas scenes in the world.\n\nThe Cologne Christmas markets collectively draw over 4 million visitors each year, making them among the most visited in all of Germany. Each market has its own character — the Cathedral Market focuses on quality artisan goods, the Heinzels Märchenweihnacht recreates a medieval scene, and the Stadtgarten Christmas Village emphasises sustainability and organic produce.\n\nCologne's central location and excellent transport connections draw visitors from across Germany, Belgium, the Netherlands and beyond. The city's vibrant atmosphere, excellent restaurants and Christmas shopping combine to make a Cologne Christmas market visit one of the most popular short breaks in Europe.\n\nFor food and craft vendors, the Cologne Christmas markets represent an extraordinary opportunity — millions of visitors, premium spending power and the prestige of one of Europe's most celebrated market settings.`,
