  date_display:'14–18 October 2026',
  description:`The Frankfurt Book Fair is the world's largest trade fair for books, media and publishing, drawing 7,500 exhibitors from 100+ countries and 280,000 visitors to Frankfurt's Messe each October. Since 1454, the fair has been the global meeting point for publishers, authors, agents, illustrators and all those who work in the world of ideas.\n\nThe fair operates on two levels — the first three days are trade-only, reserved for publishers, agents and media professionals conducting rights deals and business negotiations. The final two days open to the public, transforming the fair into a festival of reading, culture and intellectual discovery.\n\nFrankfurt Book Fair is more than a trade event — it is a cultural phenomenon. Author readings, panel discussions, award ceremonies, international pavilions and public programs make the public days one of Germany's most significant cultural events of the year. The Guest of Honour program, which changes annually, brings special focus to literature from a different country or region each year.\n\nFor vendors in the book, stationery, design, paper goods and cultural gift sectors, Frankfurt Book Fair represents an unparalleled opportunity to reach a highly educated, culturally engaged audience of 280,000 passionate readers and culture enthusiasts.`,
