  description:`The Stuttgart Wine Festival is Europe's largest open-air wine festival, held each September in Stuttgart's magnificent Schillerplatz and the surrounding historic market square. Over ten days, more than 120 Stuttgart-region wine growers present over 500 different wines — predominantly Trollinger, Lemberger, Riesling and Pinot varieties — direct to the public from traditional wooden booths.\n\nWith 1.5 million visitors and over half a million litres of wine poured, the Stuttgart Wine Festival combines the scale of a major event with the intimacy of direct producer contact. Unlike many wine fairs, Stuttgart's festival gives visitors the opportunity to speak directly with the winemakers, taste their entire range and buy directly from source.\n\nThe festival's setting in Stuttgart's beautiful baroque old town — surrounded by the Stiftskirche, Schillerplatz and the historic market square buildings — creates an atmosphere of genuine elegance. Live music, traditional Swabian food and the warmth of late-summer Stuttgart evenings make this one of Germany's most pleasurable festival experiences.\n\nFor food vendors and artisan producers, Stuttgart Wine Festival presents an affluent audience of 1.5 million visitors with strong spending power and a genuine appreciation for quality food and artisan products to accompany the excellent regional wines.`,
