  date_display:'24–28 June 2026',
  description:`Fusion Festival is Germany's most legendary alternative festival — a five-day counterculture celebration held on the grounds of a former Soviet military airfield in the Mecklenburg lake district. Founded in 1997, Fusion operates outside the commercial festival mainstream, run entirely by volunteers on a non-profit basis with a strong emphasis on community, creativity and freedom.\n\nThe festival features 20+ music stages, art installations, workshops, performance spaces and creative zones built from scratch each year by the community. Electronic music — techno, house, experimental, ambient — forms the musical heart of Fusion, with artists playing through the night and into the morning in clubs and stages scattered across the vast former airfield.\n\nFusion is famous for its DIY spirit, its rejection of corporate sponsorship, its ban on professional photography and its extraordinary community atmosphere. Up to 70,000 people build a temporary city together, creating a spirit of collective creativity that participants describe as life-changing.\n\nFor food vendors aligned with Fusion's values — organic, sustainable, community-focused — this is one of Germany's most rewarding and unusual festival opportunities. The festival's audience is highly educated, values-driven and genuinely appreciative of quality, authentic food and craft offerings.`,
