  description:`Gamescom is the world's largest gaming event, drawing 390,000 visitors to Cologne's Koelnmesse for five days of gaming announcements, playable demos, eSports tournaments and gaming culture. Since 2009, Gamescom has grown into the global gaming calendar's most important consumer event — bigger than E3, bigger than Tokyo Game Show, bigger than anything.\n\nThe event's scale is genuinely staggering — 390,000 visitors, 1,200 exhibitors from 60+ countries, 400,000 square metres of exhibition space and media coverage reaching over a billion people worldwide. Major gaming companies use Gamescom to make their most important announcements of the year, knowing the global audience is watching.\n\nThe first two days are trade-only (Gamescom Business Area), while the final three days open to the public with the vast Entertainment Area where visitors play thousands of games, watch tournaments and meet their gaming heroes. The atmosphere is electric — passionate gaming communities from across Europe and the world converge on Cologne for what is genuinely the biggest party in gaming.\n\nFor food vendors and retailers serving the gaming community, Gamescom is extraordinary — 390,000 young, tech-savvy consumers spending four days at the Koelnmesse with enormous appetite for food, energy drinks, gaming merchandise and collectibles.`,
