  title:'King\'s Day Amsterdam 2026',slug:'kings-day-amsterdam-2026-festmore',category:'festival',
  city:'Amsterdam',country:'NL',start_date:'2026-04-27',end_date:'2026-04-27',
  date_display:'27 April 2026',
  description:`King's Day (Koningsdag) is the Netherlands' greatest national celebration — a day when the entire country turns orange in honour of King Willem-Alexander's birthday. Amsterdam transforms into Europe's largest open-air party, with 800,000 people filling the streets, canals and parks for 24 hours of music, dancing, markets and orange-clad revelry.\n\nThe Vrijmarkt (Free Market) is King's Day's most beloved tradition — across the entire city, residents spread their blankets and set up stalls to sell second-hand goods, handmade crafts and all manner of curiosities in a city-wide flea market that transforms every neighbourhood into a market ground. Children and adults alike join the tradition, creating an atmosphere of community trading unlike anything else in the world.\n\nAmsterdam's canals fill with orange-decorated boats, DJs play from boat stages, and the city's parks and squares host music performances, street food markets and cultural events throughout the day and night. The celebration spans every neighbourhood from the Jordaan to the Pijp to the Plantagebuurt.\n\nFor vendors, King's Day represents one of the most extraordinary trading opportunities in Europe — 800,000 people concentrated across Amsterdam for a full day and night, enormous appetite for food, drinks, orange merchandise and everything in between, and a joyful atmosphere that makes spending irresistible.`,
