  title:'Pinkpop Festival 2026',slug:'pinkpop-festival-2026-festmore',category:'festival',
  city:'Landgraaf',country:'NL',start_date:'2026-06-19',end_date:'2026-06-21',
  date_display:'19–21 June 2026',
  description:`Pinkpop is the Netherlands' oldest and most beloved rock and pop festival, held since 1970 on the beautiful Megaland terrain in Landgraaf, Limburg. For three days across the Whitsun weekend, 70,000 fans gather for a lineup of world-class acts across four stages in what has become an annual institution of Dutch cultural life.\n\nPinkpop holds the world record as the longest-running annual pop music festival, a distinction it has held since 1975. The festival's 50+ year history means generations of Dutch families have attended together — parents bringing children who will one day bring their own children to the same grounds.\n\nThe festival's setting in the rolling hills of South Limburg is unusually scenic for a Dutch festival — the gentle landscape of the Limburg countryside provides a green, pleasant backdrop for what is one of the Netherlands' largest annual events. Past Pinkpop headliners include U2, Rolling Stones, Bruce Springsteen, Metallica, Foo Fighters and Red Hot Chili Peppers.\n\nFor vendors, Pinkpop's 70,000 attendees in a concentrated terrain over three days provides exceptional trading conditions. The festival's loyal audience is well-acquainted with the event's food and drink offering and knows what to expect — quality, variety and genuine value.`,
